This paper deals with Delay Tolerant Networks (DTNs) and their routing policies, which are related to networking (cs.NI) and information theory (cs.IT). The paper also addresses heterogeneous mobility patterns and multiple wireless transmission technologies, which are related to machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.MA). The algorithmic approaches proposed in the paper involve optimization and approximation techniques, which are related to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and control systems (cs.SY).
